(Reuters) - Colorado became the first state in the U.S. to abolish anonymous donation of sperm and eggs, as well as set other restrictions. Legal experts Kimberly Mutcherson of Rutgers Law School and Naomi Cahn of the University of Virginia School of Law as well as Jillian Phillips of the U.S. Donor Conceived Council discuss potential scenarios stemming from this novel development in reproductive law. Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles. Thomson Reuters Alex Cohen produces multimedia projects on legal trends, key cases, and industry issues. He can be reached at alex.cohen@thomsonreuters.com. You can follow him on Twitter @alexlcohen.